node.title: Phin live q&a with Phin’s dad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Phineas Tyrion Holly on August 14, 2021. May be an image of cat.

node.text:
This little megaphone makes his presence known in the mornings!Can’t oversleep breakfast, ma! Good thing he’s cute 🥰 happy Saturday everyone!!———————————————————————————
Phin has a condition called cerebellar hypoplasia. This means that the part of his brain that coordinates movement never fully developed. He's not in any pain, and he won't get worse over time, though there also aren't any treatments that would help him. He had a difficult time getting enough food in his system as a kitten, experiencing Fading kitten syndrome, but his foster mom, @fosterkittys , nurtured him with a lot of love and care, and he was able to grow into the wonderful cat he is now. 😻 Phin adapts to his condition by walking with his paws a bit wider, leaning against the wall for support, and using claws to climb up and down things. Phin is a very happy kitty who loves playing with his siblings (Tyrion the cat, and Holly the Airedale Terrier), eating meals and treats, and cuddling with his parents. 😻 
———————————————————————————
#phineasthecat #cerebellarhypoplasia #catsofinstagram #phinstagram

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Phineas Tyrion Holly on August 09, 2021. May be an image of cat and indoor.

node.text:
Monday morning Phin! Parents have a goofy schedule today, so Phin got his breakfast at 5:30 am... Time to nap until dinner! 😸 Also, are you from Pennsylvania and think having a CH cat JUST LIKE PHIN would be amazing (hint: it is amazing to have a cat like Phin!)? Check out the latest post from @sventhespeedy, who is in foster care in Philadelphia and ready for his perfect forever home! The similarities are striking! ❤️

node.text: Big news! Our sweet girl Holly completed her cancer treatment today! She's been living life to the fullest while on chemotherapy, following her spleen removal surgery months ago. Just this past week, she got to camp with family and their dog, @welshiesadie, in Arapaho Bay, Colorado. She played on the beach, hiked, kayaked, and had a great overall time! We're so grateful to everyone who supported us through his difficult journey. It's hard to put into words how much we appreciate everyone. We plan to do checkups every 3 months for the next year or so to make sure the cancer doesn't return elsewhere following the chemo. But, for now, we're happy to spoil her and celebrate with her. Back in March, we never thought we'd be at this point right now, and it's just amazing to see her being so happy and energetic again! We have @sugarhousevet, @medvet, @puddleduck_90, and all of you who supported us to thank for getting her through!  #hollytheairedale #cancersucks #airedalesofinstagram

node.text: Apologies for our absence! We were camping in Colorado with Holly for much of this past week and just got back last night! The kitties were very happy to see us after spending the week being cared for by friends of ours, and Tyrion has been particularly chirpy since we've been back! We're hopeful to have a great update on Holly on Wednesday, so fingers crossed for that! #phineasthecat #Tyrionthecat  #cerebellarhypoplasia

node.text:
One of Phin's favorite things (aside from food) is lounging around on his parents' bed and having conversations with whoever walks into the room, particularly if it's his dad. 😸
———————————————————————————
Phin has a condition called cerebellar hypoplasia. This means that the part of his brain that coordinates movement never fully developed. He's not in any pain, and he won't get worse over time, though there also aren't any treatments that would help him. He had a difficult time getting enough food in his system as a kitten, experiencing Fading kitten syndrome, but his foster mom, @fosterkittys , nurtured him with a lot of love and care, and he was able to grow into the wonderful cat he is now. 😻 Phin adapts to his condition by walking with his paws a bit wider, leaning against the wall for support, and using claws to climb up and down things. Phin is a very happy kitty who loves playing with his siblings (Tyrion the cat, and Holly the Airedale Terrier), eating meals and treats, and cuddling with his parents. 😻 
———————————————————————————
#phineasthecat #cerebellarhypoplasia #catsofinstagram #phinstagram

node.text:
This very good girl had a fun time in the Cassia Mountains in Sawtooth National Forest while mom and dad took a work-cation to get off internet access and finish up some writing for work. Holly has completed 5 of 6 chemo doses and will be all done in 2 1/2 weeks! It's been a long road since finding out she had cancer, getting her a splenectomy, and proceeding with chemo. But, but we're so happy with how she's doing and optimistic for the future! 😻
#hollytheairedale #airedalesofinstagram #cancersucks

node.text:
When you're just in the kitchen to do dishes but Phin decides you're going to feed him dinner 4 hours early. 😼
———————————————————————————
Phin has a condition called cerebellar hypoplasia. This means that the part of his brain that coordinates movement never fully developed. He's not in any pain, and he won't get worse over time, though there also aren't any treatments that would help him. He had a difficult time getting enough food in his system as a kitten, experiencing Fading kitten syndrome, but his foster mom, @fosterkittys , nurtured him with a lot of love and care, and he was able to grow into the wonderful cat he is now. 😻 Phin adapts to his condition by walking with his paws a bit wider, leaning against the wall for support, and using claws to climb up and down things. Phin is a very happy kitty who loves playing with his siblings (Tyrion the cat, and Holly the Airedale Terrier), eating meals and treats, and cuddling with his parents. 😻 
———————————————————————————
